\b Discussion (Part 2)\b0\par
Gate charge values are expected to increase with higher gate drive voltage. Differences between HS and LS measurements may occur due to probing constraints and reference conditions. High-side measurement is sensitive to common-mode disturbances and requires careful probing. The stated probe capacitance (\~1 pF) is considered as an error source because fast dv/dt can create displacement currents that affect the measurement.\par

